    "description": "Kogi Corporation manufactures and sells casting roll-related products, environmental equipment, and friction materials in Japan and internationally. The company operates through Casting Field, Environment Field/Environmental Engineering, and Environment Field/Functional Materials segments. It offers various rolling rolls, such as steel plates, wire rods, steel bars, H-shaped steel, angle steel, channel steel, and deformed steel bars; steel castings for steel ingot molds and automotive press molds; and rum, cylinder, manhole cover, iron cover, and grating. It also provides continuous cast-iron rods and general casting products. In addition, the company offers blowers, transvectors, vortex coolers, oil skimmer, gas cooler/refrigerated air dryer, and air filter/dedicated adapter; KC metal fibers; and waste incinerators, recycling equipment, and superheated steam application equipment. Further, it offers ACE automatic molding machine, V process automatic molding machine, gray cast iron, spheroidal graphite cast iron, and press die casting, as well as TGC600 technology. Additionally, the company provides mold products, such as bed, frame, table, molding board, column, housing, gear housing, and gear casing; heat resistant castings, and steel related casting mold, molding board, and throat metals; other molds, sinker, tundish cover, throat cover, and alloy mold; and cast-iron rods under the Dense Bar name. Kogi Corporation was founded in 1916 and is headquartered in Himeji, Japan."
